  <sect2>
    <title>Kernel Configuration</title>

    <para>
      Enable the following options in the kernel configuration and recompile the
      kernel if necessary:
    </para>

<screen><literal>File systems  ---&gt;
  Network File Systems  ---&gt;
    CIFS support (advanced network filesystem, SMBFS successor): Y or M</literal></screen>

    <indexterm zone="cifs-utils">
      <primary sortas="d-cifs-utils">cifs-utils</primary>
    </indexterm>

  </sect2>

  <sect2>
    <title>Installation</title>

    <para>
      Install cifs-utils by running the following commands:
    </para>

<screen><userinput>./configure --prefix=/usr &amp;&amp;
make</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      Now, as the <systemitem class="username">root</systemitem> user:
    </para>

<screen role="root"><userinput>make install</userinput></screen>

  </sect2>

